(((((( MASTER-SLAVE CONCEPT IN JENKINS ))))))

* MASTER("CONTROLLER") 
This is the main Jenkins Server. It handles the web interface , Job scheduling ,Dispatching builds to slaves(AGENTS), Monitoring slaves (AGENTS), 
Collecting Build Results .

* SLAVE ("AGENT")
-> These are the other servers connected to master 
-> These are only active when a job is assigned to them.

EXAMPLE : IMAGINES JENKINS IS A MANAGER IN AN OFFICE :
-> The Manager(MASTER) give out tasks(JOBS) to employees(SLAVE/AGENTS)
-> Employees do the actual work .
-> The Manager just assign tasks and checks if they are done .



